[An interactive ProMED HealthMap of the state can be found at: http://healthmap.org/r/1-eG.]

******
[2] Cholera - China
Date: Mon 16 Dec 2013
Source: Bernama [edited]
http://www.bernama.com.my/bernama/v7/wn/newsworld.php?id=1001550


A total of 1393 people died of infectious diseases on the Chinese mainland in November 2013, the National Health and Family Planning Commission announced on Mon 16 Dec 2013, Xinhua news agency reported.

A total of 549 429 infectious disease cases were reported in November 2013, it said. Among them, 2 cases of cholera were reported, but none resulted in death.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Although classically referred to as Asiatic cholera, many more cases occur outside of that continent, usually in sub-Saharan Africa. The outbreak of _Vibrio cholerae_ in Haiti beginning in October 2010 has made a large impact, however, in the worldwide distribution of reported cases. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1zaU.]
